result.name: Café de Coral

reviews.text: A popular gathering fast food venue for locals and visitors from Mainland China alike. As such, it is always overcrowded with people, creating a queue both at the order counters and at the food collection spot. The large number of customers has made cleaning up a challenge for the staff.  One may have to wait quite a while for the collection of used dishes and trays even if one is lucky to get a seat. Food comes hot and the quality is just about average. The afternoon tea menu is of particular interest to lovers of instant noodles as it takes up at least 40% of your choice. Coffee is surely one of the best found among fast food venues and is great value for money.
Fast service , cheap food, chained fast food shop
Is a good place to eat with family and friends..
Friendly and helpful staff as always. Food is ok if you don’t mind it’s heavily ladened with MSG. Perhaps it’s just so at this branch.
Tasty and fast. Suggest not to eat the "Chinese Baked Porkchop Rice"after 7 or before 5 as they are only made ready-to-serve and not fresh out the oven.
